ist "  or a  " communist "  if he were college brat today .now on the other hand ,  try to find anywhere in this book ,  the words  " murderer ,  "  or even  " extremist "  in front of names like mao tse tung ,  or che guevara or tom hayden ,  to name a few .   there is a good reason for that ,  but i will leave it to your imagination ,  the reason why .in summary ,  should you decide to read this book ,  take it with a grain of salt ,  or better yet some motion-sickness pills because unless you are prone to the same convictions as our professor lytle is ,  you're going to need a barf-bag
